  "purpose": "Declares, per operation family, which AutoCAD execution host each family runs in and whether that host is headless (unattended) or attended (interactive session). Bridges the two pre-existing 4-value host vocabularies: the alias map's execution_host_class {dbx, coreconsole, arx_adapter, full_autocad} and the catalog's engine_tier {objectdbx_capable, native_arx_only, managed_also, accoreconsole_lisp_also}. These are NOT the same axis: host_class = WHERE it runs; engine_tier = WHAT API surface it needs. The crosswalk below is the new intelligence v2 adds.",
